Larson Evans

Skilled Software Developer

Dedicated to building high-quality, efficient applications with expertise in front-end and back-end technologies.

Phone: 404-907-9942 | LinkedIn: linkedin.com/in/larson-evans-72687b178/ | Email: larsonevans21@gmail.com

Education

Mercer University

Bachelors: Computer Science (Graduation May 2023)

Programming Languages: C#, CSS, Java, JavaScript, HTML, PHP, Python, PL/SQL, SQL

Frameworks & Libraries: Spring Boot, React, Selenium, PostgreSQL

Development Tools: Azure DevOps, Ubuntu, Docker, Git

Clearance: Secret

Professional Summary

Experienced in designing, developing, and optimizing web applications with front-end and back-end technologies. Demonstrated expertise in data processing, database integration, and user interface enhancements to ensure high-quality application performance.

Work Experience

Mercer Engineering Research Center - Software Developer

June 2023 – November 2024

  • Performed full-stack development tasks on AIRCAT, including creating webpages and modifying database packages using C#, HTML, SQL, PL/SQL, and Python.
  • Collaborated to design and implement a workflow for managing critical safety items for the C-130 aircraft.
  • Improved system performance and usability for AIRCAT's DTADS DASHBOARD, enhancing data analysis capabilities for the Air Force.
  • Applied Python libraries (Pandas, CUDA Toolkit, seaborn, matplotlib) to create a model accuracy truth table and containerized an AI model with Docker.
Warner Robins Air Force Base - Software Developer Intern

May 2021 – May 2023

  • Preprocessed data and trained machine learning models for SOA-ESB, developing early warning systems to prevent server crashes.
  • Enhanced PEER, a collaboration platform for satellite analysis, by implementing a session chat feature with Spring Boot, React, and MongoDB.
Mercer on Mission - STEM Teacher Volunteer, South Africa

June 2022 - July 2022

  • Delivered innovative STEM lessons, teaching programming using Jeroo, Python, Google Scripts, and Python turtles to middle and high school students.

Projects

Long Short-Term Memory Stock Predictor Application

Spring 2023

  • Developed a neural network using TensorFlow to predict stock prices based on historical data.
  • Implemented features such as moving averages and technical indicators to improve prediction accuracy, achieving 48% prediction accuracy.
Job Queue Simulation

Spring 2022

  • Developed an application simulating an OS job queue, providing metrics such as arrival, wait, and turnaround times.
  • Built the program using linked lists, pointers, and the Queue ADT.
Employee Database

Spring 2022

  • Built a personnel database for employee wages and information, leveraging object-oriented principles.
  • Supported actions like adding new employees, managing payroll, and calculating wages, with scalability and maintainability in mind.
